Companion (bottom-screen rest/wait) — export + control bridge for the native WaitDialog
(GM_Rest). Mirrors companion-repair-export.patch. The native WaitDialog is hidden while
GM_Rest is in DS mode (companion-hide-gamewindows-on-dsmode.patch); the picker (mode, date,
hour selection) moves to the bottom screen, but the ENGINE still runs the actual fade +
progress-bar time advance (and sleep interruption / level-up) on the top screen once a
rest/wait is confirmed — that logic is not reimplemented.

Outbound, emitted from WaitDialog::setPtr → companionExportOpen() (onOpen, which builds the
date caption, runs BEFORE setPtr, and setCanRest() in setPtr has just set mSleeping + the
rest-text caption, so both are current):
  COMPANION_SLEEP_OPEN:<mode>|<dateString>|<warning>
    mode       = "rest" (mSleeping) or "wait"
    dateString = the resolved mDateTimeText caption, e.g. "24 Last Seed (Day 9) 10 a.m."
    warning    = the mRestText caption in WAIT mode (illegal-rest / werewolf message), else ""
  COMPANION_SLEEP_CLOSED on close.
Guarded by getRestEnabled() (matches onOpen's own gate). The hard-reject cases (enemies
nearby / underwater / in air without a bed) pop the mode in setPtr before this point, so no
OPEN is emitted and no overlay shows — native's own messageBox handles those.

Inbound: a file-static gCompanionWaitDialog (set in the ctor) plus two extern "C" bridges —
companionSleep(hours) / companionSleepCancel — let drainCompanionCommands drive the picker
from CMP:sleep / CMP:sleep_cancel. companionStartWait(hours) calls the native startWaiting()
(the whole fade/advance/interrupt/level-up path); companionCancelWait() routes through
onCancelButtonClicked (removeGuiMode(GM_Rest)). Both no-op while a time-advance is running.
Each bridge no-ops unless containsMode(GM_Rest) (stale-window guard).

Close signal: the native window is HIDDEN the moment the mode opens in DS mode, so the usual
visible->hidden onClose() never fires. COMPANION_SLEEP_CLOSED is emitted explicitly, once-
guarded (gCompanionSleepSessionOpen), from every end path: companionStartWait (confirm — the
picker's job is done, the top screen takes over the advance), onCancelButtonClicked (Cancel,
native or companion), and exit() (B/Escape).
